    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4491" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θεσπέσιος</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θεός</span>, root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σεπ,
            ἔσπετε</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">divinely uttered</span> or
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">uttering</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θεσπεσίῃ</span>,
          ‘by divine decree,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 2.367</span></i>),
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">divine;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀοιδή,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 2.600</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            Σειρῆνες</span>, ‘heavenlysinging,’ <i><span class="en">Od.
            12.158</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; βηλός</span>, ‘of heaven,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 1.591</span></i>; then of anything
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">prodigious, vast, wondrous, mighty</span>, a storm, clamor,
          panic, etc.—Adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θεσπεσίως</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.637</span></i>. 
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
